race.description: Book For Amateur Cup Sat 23rd May Handicap (55)
race.comment: MARELLITY (11) was an impressive maiden winner over 1100m here last time, cruising home by over 2 lengths. Now that the penny has dropped, she can take the next step immediately. LITTLE PINKER (8) showed sharp early speed and raced handy throughout before tiring to fifth over 1280m at Emerald 3 weeks ago. She is peaking now and can figure in the top 3 this time. BOOM CRUSHER (1) is as honest as they come, but can't seem to win another race. He resumes from a spell and has to be respected. Each-way. RUM RUNNER (5) produced another moderate showing last time, finishing well back over 1200m at Rockhampton. He is worth another chance. RUM RUMBLE (3) finished strongly when beaten a long neck last time at Rockhampton and should be hitting the line hard again. Include in all top 4 combos. LOOMING LEGEND (12) ran second at Townsville two back but wasn't as effective last start over 1200m at Rockhampton, finishing out of the money but not too far off the winner. Each-way value.
